> Hi, Mark.  I thought you'd like to know what uses RIPEM is being put to.
> 
> I'm starting a business that sells computer versions of books over the
>  'net, started with an email client -- that client is based upon RIPEM.
> 
> Essentially, what I've done is hardcoded our public key into RIPEM, and
>  hardcoded various options in.  On top of that, I generate an order form
>  and call sendmail.
> 
> Thanks for releasing this stuff to the public domain -- it's made our
>  getting started much easier!  (I'm sure it'll diverge from RIPEM as
>  time goes by, but RIPEM being PD allows us to just sign a contract w/
>  PKP and go...)
